        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="vertical-align:top; height:86px;">
          <para styleclass="Interface2"><text styleclass="Interface2" translate="true">Motion-Law Coefficients</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Block" rowcount="4" colcount="2">
            <tr style="vertical-align:middle">
              <td style="width:203px;">
                <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">Velocity Coefficient : </text></para>
              </td>
              <td style="width:128px;">
                <para styleclass="Popup Box"><equation styleclass="Popup Box" font-size="28" translate="true"><![CDATA[C_{v} = 1.333]]></equation></para>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="vertical-align:middle">
              <td style="width:203px;">
                <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">Acceleration Coefficient : </text></para>
              </td>
              <td style="width:128px;">
                <para styleclass="Popup Box"><equation styleclass="Popup Box" font-size="28" translate="true"><![CDATA[C_{a}=8.378]]></equation></para>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="vertical-align:middle">
              <td style="width:203px;">
                <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">Jerk Coefficient : </text></para>
              </td>
              <td style="width:128px;">
                <para styleclass="Popup Box"><equation styleclass="Popup Box" font-size="28" translate="true"><![CDATA[C_{j} = 105.276]]></equation></para>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="vertical-align:middle">
              <td style="width:203px;">
                <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">Jerk at Cross-over : </text></para>
              </td>
              <td style="width:128px;">
                <para styleclass="Popup Box"><equation styleclass="Popup Box" font-size="28" translate="true"><![CDATA[C_{Jc} =105.276]]></equation></para>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Interface2"><text styleclass="Interface2" translate="true">Application Notes</text><text styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_" translate="true">:</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Block" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td>
                <para styleclass="VariableName"><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">Dynamic Performance</text></para>
                <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">This Motion-Law is recommended in applications where you need the peak velocity to be low when compared to others. </text></para>
                <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">It has a large Peak Acceleration, with a short duration, thus more likely to induce vibrations.</text></para>
                <para styleclass="VariableName"><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">Pressure Angle Considerations</text></para>
                <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">It gives a relatively low pressure angle - because of its low peak velocity.</text></para>
                <para styleclass="VariableName"><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">Drive Torques</text></para>
                <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">This Motion-Law is not recommended in many applications as it will give a sudden change in torque. The input transmission rigidity would need to be high.</text></para>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
